      • FileSystem

        public FileSystem(java.io.File root,
          java.lang.String name,
          java.lang.String type,
          boolean requireAuthentication,
          boolean acceptDuplicateUIDs,
          boolean setReadable,
          boolean setWritable,
          java.util.List<ImageQualifiers> qualifiers)
        Create a FileSystem within a specific root directory.
        Parameters:
        root - the base directory of all FileSystems.
        name - the name of this FileSystem. This name is filtered by the makeFSName method before use.
        type - the way the directory tree is to be structured:
        • "none" - all study directories appear as first generation children of the root directory (e.g., root/studyName).
        • "year" - all study directories appear as children of a year directory (e.g., root/year/studyName).
        • "month" - all study directories appear as children of a year/month directory (e.g., root/year/month/studyName).
        • "week" - all study directories appear as children of a year/week directory (e.g., root/year/week/studyName).
        • "day" - all study directories appear as children of a year/day directory (e.g., root/year/day/studyName).
        requireAuthentication - true if accesses to this FileSystem require authentication; false otherwise.
        setReadable - true if files and directories in this FileSystem are to be world readable.
        setWritable - true if files and directories in this FileSystem are to be world writable.
        qualifiers - the list of qualifiers for the creation of JPEG images when a DICOM image is stored.

    • Method Detail

      • allowsAccessBy

        public boolean allowsAccessBy(org.rsna.server.User user)
        Determine whether a specific user can access this FileSystem. The rules are applied in this order, with the first matching rule winning:
        1. If authentication is not required, all users are granted access, even ones who are not authenticated (e.g. user == null).
        2. If authentication is required:
          • If the user is not authenticated (user == null) access is denied.
          • If the FileSystem name is "__default", access is granted.
          • If the username is the same as the name of the FileSystem, access is granted.
          • If the user has the "read" privilege, access is granted.
          • If the username appears in the guest list, access is granted.
          • In all other cases, access is denied.
        Parameters:
        user - the User requesting access.
        Returns:
        true if this FileSystem can be accessed by the specified user; false otherwise.

      • makeFSName

        public static java.lang.String makeFSName(java.lang.String name)
        Filter a name to create one which is acceptable for use as a FileSystem name. The filter removes all characters except underscore, a-z, A-Z, and 0-9. If the result is an empty string, it assigns the name "__default".
        Parameters:
        name - a proposed name for a FileSystem.
        Returns:
        the filtered name.
